  "high_concept": "Burning Vows subverts enemies-to-lovers by forcing Lena Castillo—a sharp-tongued NYC divorce attorney who built a living on other people's breakups—onto the sun-drenched Amalfi Coast to co-plan her best friend's wedding with Marco Vitale, the infuriatingly charming best man and the man from her unresolved one-night stand. Shared villas and late-night confessions peel away Lena's legal armor as Marco's private family tragedy echoes her terrified certainty about becoming her mother, while a hidden set of divorce papers tied to the groom's parents threatens to either validate her cynicism or wreck the celebration and the fragile trust between them. Confronted with the power to expose the truth or protect the wedding, Lena faces the cost of self-preservation—certainty—or risking everything for a love she keeps insisting doesn't exist.",
