  "characters": [
    {
      "name": "Lena Castillo",
      "role": "Protagonist - Guarded divorce attorney learning to risk vulnerability",
      "physical_description": "31, Cuban-American with warm olive skin that bronzes easily in the Italian sun. Dark chocolate curls that reach her shoulders, perpetually escaping whatever clip or band she uses to tame them—she has a habit of shoving escaped tendrils behind her ears when frustrated. Expressive dark brown eyes that can shift from laser-focused courtroom intensity to vulnerable uncertainty in seconds. Athletic build from stress-running through Central Park at dawn, with strong shoulders and calloused hands from gripping her phone too tightly during difficult cases. Favors crisp blazers and pencil skirts in NYC, but in Amalfi gravitates toward flowing sundresses that make her feel exposed. Has a small scar on her left palm from broken glass the night her parents' marriage imploded.",
      "personality": "Razor-sharp intellect wrapped in defensive humor—uses wit like a scalpel to deflect before anyone gets too close. Fiercely loyal to the few people who've earned her trust, particularly Sofia. Perfectionist who masks anxiety with over-preparation and control. Deeply empathetic despite her cynical profession, which is why divorce cases gut her more than she admits. Stubborn pride that makes apologizing feel like swallowing glass. Secret romantic who's buried that part of herself so deep she's almost convinced it doesn't exist. Switches to rapid Spanish when overwhelmed, emotional, or trying to process something she can't face in English.",
      "backstory": "Grew up watching her parents' passionate marriage turn toxic—screaming fights, thrown dishes, her mother's tears behind closed doors. At 16, found her father's affair evidence and kept the secret for months, believing she could fix things. When her mother finally left, Lena blamed herself for not speaking up sooner. Threw herself into academics, then law school, specializing in divorce as both penance and protection. The one-night stand with Marco three years ago happened during the worst case of her career—a custody battle that ended with a child in the hospital. Marco saw through her armor for one night, and she's been terrified of that vulnerability ever since.",
      "goals": "External: Successfully co-plan Sofia's wedding without destroying her best friend's happiness. Internal: Learn to distinguish between protecting herself and sabotaging herself, find the courage to want love instead of just surviving it.",
      "arc": "Starts as a woman who's convinced herself that cynicism equals wisdom and that seeing through romantic illusions makes her strong. Through forced proximity with Marco and witnessing genuine love around her, she discovers that her 'realism' is actually fear wearing a sophisticated disguise. Ends as someone who chooses vulnerability not because it's safe, but because it's the only way to truly live.",
      "voice": "Sharp, quick wit with legal metaphors peppered throughout ('I object,' 'sustained,' 'leading the witness'). Drops into Spanish when emotional: 'Dios mío,' 'Ay, por favor,' 'Qué desastre.' Self-deprecating humor to deflect serious moments. Clipped, professional tone when defensive, but voice softens and sentences flow longer when she's genuinely moved. Butchers Italian pronunciation endearingly.",
      "signature_behaviors": "Tugs at escaped curls when nervous. Straightens already-straight objects when anxious. Goes for runs to think through problems. Checks her phone compulsively during emotional conversations. Makes lists for everything, including pros and cons of feelings. Switches languages mid-sentence when flustered. Crosses arms when feeling attacked, uncrosses them when ready to trust.",
      "relationships": "Sofia: Best friend since law school, the sister she chose. Marco: The man who cracked her open and the one she's most afraid of. Gianna: Initially sees her as the enemy but slowly recognizes a kindred spirit in protection and loss. Her mother: Complicated love mixed with terror of becoming her."
    },
    {
      "name": "Marco Vitale",
      "role": "Love interest - Charming man hiding devastating guilt",
      "physical_description": "34, Italian-American with the kind of Mediterranean looks that make tourists stare—olive skin that's always slightly sun-kissed, thick dark hair that curls at the nape of his neck and around his ears when it gets too long. Warm brown eyes with gold flecks that become more pronounced when he laughs, which he does often despite his hidden pain. Tall and lean with broad shoulders, callused hands from weekend carpentry projects he uses to quiet his mind. Has a habit of running those hands through his hair when thinking. Small scar through his left eyebrow from a childhood accident with his younger brother. Dresses casually but well—linen shirts rolled to the elbows, dark jeans that fit perfectly, expensive watch that was his brother's.",
      "personality": "Naturally charismatic with an easy laugh and the ability to make anyone feel like the most interesting person in the room. Deeply family-oriented but carries crushing guilt over his brother's death that he hides behind charm and helpfulness. Perceptive about others' pain because he's intimately familiar with his own. Patient and persistent when he wants something, but respectful of boundaries. Has a tendency to fix things and people, which sometimes comes across as controlling. Genuinely kind but struggles to forgive himself for past mistakes.",
      "backstory": "Grew up in a tight-knit Italian-American family in Boston. Always the responsible older brother to Luca, who was born when Marco was 15. Felt more like Luca's father than brother, especially after their dad died when Luca was 12. The night Luca died in a car accident at 19, he'd called Marco for a ride home from a party, but Marco was on a date and let it go to voicemail. Luca drove drunk and crashed. Marco has spent the last four years believing that if he'd just answered his phone, his brother would be alive. Threw himself into work as a successful architect but struggles with relationships because he can't bear the thought of failing someone else he loves.",
      "goals": "External: Plan the perfect wedding for his cousin Dante and prove to his family he can still be trusted with important things. Internal: Learn to forgive himself and believe he deserves happiness, find the courage to fight for Lena despite her walls.",
      "arc": "Starts as a man who uses charm and helpfulness to mask his guilt and self-punishment. Through his connection with Lena and confronting his family's grief, he learns that carrying guilt doesn't honor his brother's memory—living fully does. Ends as someone who can accept forgiveness and offer it to others.",
